<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Malmros</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Colon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-06"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                        1903</hi>.</date><lb/>(Received 4.50
                                p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Tranquillity absolute in Colon. Porfirio Melendez appointed governor
                                of this province. Proclaimed Republic of Panama at Colon prefectura
                                at 10 o’clock a.m. English and French consuls present. I arrived
                                after proclamation, and upon my suggestion I told governor that
                                presence of consuls must not be looked upon as recognition of
                                revolutionary state by their respective Governments. Melendez sent
                                steam launch to Bocas del Toro to proclaim independence.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Malmros.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>